  "prompt": "What are the best books of all time?",
  "response": "Determining the best books of all time is subjective, as individual tastes and preferences vary. However, there are several classics and critically acclaimed works that have stood the test of time and are often included in lists of the \"best\" or \"most important\" books. Here are some commonly mentioned titles:\n\n1. **\"To Kill a Mockingbird\" by Harper Lee**\n2. **\"1984\" by George Orwell**\n3. **\"Pride and Prejudice\" by Jane Austen**\n4. **\"The Great Gatsby\" by F. Scott Fitzgerald**\n5. **\"Moby-Dick\" by Herman Melville**\n6. **\"One Hundred Years of Solitude\" by Gabriel Garc\u00eda M\u00e1rquez**\n7. **\"War and Peace\" by Leo Tolstoy**\n8. **\"The Catcher in the Rye\" by J.D. Salinger**\n9. **\"Crime and Punishment\" by Fyodor Dostoevsky**\n10. **\"The Brothers Karamazov\" by Fyodor Dostoevsky**\n11. **\"In Search of Lost Time\" by Marcel Proust**\n12. **\"Middlemarch\" by George Eliot**\n13. **\"Ulysses\" by James Joyce**\n14. **\"Anna Karenina\" by Leo Tolstoy**\n15. **\"Brave New World\" by Aldous Huxley**\n16. **\"Wuthering Heights\" by Emily Bront\u00eb**\n17. **\"Jane Eyre\" by Charlotte Bront\u00eb**\n18. **\"Don Quixote\" by Miguel de Cervantes**\n19. **\"The Catch-22\" by Joseph Heller**\n20. **\"The Odyssey\" by Homer**\n\nThese books are widely recognized for their literary significance, powerful storytelling, and influence on literature and culture.",
